Notes:
1 fall on onsight go. Sent through the first crux, but fell on the bulge first go. Went next time with very powerful Gaston move

Crux 1: left foot needs to end on edge just below huge rail. Right foot on black rubber big foot. Left thumb press, right crimp. Left up to 3 finger positive crimp, right up to left Gaston crimp, big move to sidepull jug. 

Crux 2: get massive rail just over bulge (it is huge) left hand Gaston. right foot high onto big foot, pull hips in really tight. Must keep core tight! Big move to jug with right hand (do not get suckered into underclings! Hold right next to bolt is very big)

Notes:
Led every pitch with Jordan following

Onsight 2, 6.
Redpoint 1, 5
Fell/hung 3,4,7

P1: fingercrack is less than vertical. Lock and smear and you’re by a wide margin strong enough to get to the hand jam/stem rest at top of fingers

Incinerator: STAY TIGHT! climb fast and find finger locks to place. Cannot sow it up. Pull hips into wall to place. Would a right leg Drop knee work?? Climbing is easy, placing is strenuous. Good hand jams and a .75 near top of crack

Boulder problem: right hand undercling, right foot jam, left hand palm press, left foot edge -> left foot onto arete, trust it, right foot onto sloper below undercling, right hand Gaston undercling, stand up to jug

Pitch 5: hidden jug at most awkward part, right before thin hands/overhang (in the hole, can’t see before committing)

Pitch 7: crank on thin hands (don’t try to ring lock), get feet up, tight hand jam
